  <title>Cogl.Onscreen.prototype.get_resizable</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function get_resizable(): <link xref="Cogl.Bool">Cogl.Bool</link> {
    // Gjs wrapper for cogl_onscreen_get_resizable()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Lets you query whether <code>onscreen</code> has been marked as resizable via
the <link xref="Cogl.Onscreen.set_resizable"/> api.</p>  <p>By default, if possible, a <code>onscreen</code> will be created by Cogl
as non resizable, but it is not guaranteed that this is always
possible for all window systems.</p>  <p>&lt;note&gt;If cogl_onscreen_set_resizable(<code>onscreen</code>, <code>true</code>) has been
previously called then this function will return <code>true</code>, but it's
possible that the current windowing system being used does not
support window resizing (consider fullscreen windows on a phone or
a TV). This function is not aware of whether resizing is truly
meaningful with your window system, only whether the <code>onscreen</code> has
been marked as resizable.&lt;/note&gt;</p>
  <p>Since 2.0</p>
<terms>
<item>
<title><code>Returns</code></title>
  <p>Returns whether <code>onscreen</code> has been marked as
              resizable or not.</p>
</item>
</terms>

